pages.general_notes_verbatim:
STEEL NOTES
1) ALL DIMENSIONS ARE IN INCHES UNLESS NOTED OTHERWISE.
2) WHERE WELD SYMBOL IS SHOWN, ASSUME FILLET ALL
AROUND, WITH SIZE EQUAL TO THE LESSER OF 1/4" OR THE
MINIMUM THICKNESS OF ADJOINING FACES, UNLESS NOTED.
3) STRUCTURAL STEEL PLATES, ANGLES, AND CHANNELS SHALL
CONFORM TO CSA G40.21-2004, G40.21-350W CLASS C FOR HSS
AND W SECTIONS.
4) WELDING SHALL CONFORM TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF CSA
STANDARDS W59 AND SHALL BE UNDERTAKEN BY A FABRICATOR
AND ERECTOR FULLY APPROVED BY THE CANADIAN WELDING
BUREAU TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF CSA STANDARDS W47,
DIVISION 1 OR DIVISION 2.1.
5) FIELD VERIFY ALL DIMENSIONS PRIOR TO MANUFACTURING.
6) ALL STRUCTURAL STEEL TO BE FINISHED AS APPROVED BY
THE CONTRACTOR/OWNER.
7) ALL HARDWARE TO BE TORQUED BY TURN-OF-NUT METHOD
AS PER 5619.3.7.2, AND TABLE 7.

DESIGN LOADS
1) DESIGN LOADS ARE UNFACTORED UNLESS NOTED OTHERWISE:
A) DEAD LOADS: SELF-WEIGHT OF STEEL
B) LIVE LOAD (MAX.CAPACITY): AS PER LOAD TABLE ON THE
FIRST PAGE OF THIS DRAWING PACKAGE
pages.page_overview_summary: This sheet provides detailed weldment drawings for the NC Tooling Cabinet, including ISO partial views. It includes comprehensive steel notes and design load specifications, ensuring compliance with CSA standards. The sheet emphasizes the importance of field verification and proper welding practices.
